Project Aim
The aim of this project is to develop a "Food Ordering Mobile Application (FOODSPOT)" using MIT App Inventor.
The application allows users to register and log in, browse different food categories such as Veg, Coffee, and Desserts, select food items, add them to a cart, view item details and price, and place an order using Cash on Delivery (COD). The app provides a simple and user-friendly interface for ordering food and generates a final confirmation screen after placing the order.

Technical Algorithms (Screen-by-Screen)
Screen 1: Login Screen

Algorithm:
User enters Email and Password.
When Login button is clicked:
Check if EmailTextBox.Text = "" OR PasswordTextBox.Text = "".
If empty → show message "Enter Email & Password".
Else → open Home Screen.

Screen 2: Signup Screen

Algorithm:
User enters Email and Password.
When Register button is clicked:
Check if EmailTextBox.Text = "" OR PasswordTextBox.Text = "".
If empty → show message "Enter Email & Password".
Else → open Home Screen.
(Optional) Data can be stored using TinyDB.

Screen 3: Home Screen (Dashboard)

Algorithm:
Display three main categories:
Veg 
Coffee 
Desserts 
Wait for user selection.
On button click:
If Veg clicked → open Veg Screen.
If Coffee clicked → open Coffee Screen.
If Desserts clicked → open Desserts Screen.

Screen 4: Veg Items Screen

Algorithm:
Display Veg food items with:
Item Name
Price (Label, not editable)
Add to Cart button
When "Add to Cart" is clicked:
Store item name and price using TinyDB or StartValue.
Open Cart Screen.

Screen 5: Coffee Items Screen

Algorithm:
Display coffee items with name and price.
Provide Add to Cart button.
On click:
Store selected item details.
Open Cart Screen.

Screen 6: Desserts Items Screen

Algorithm:
Display dessert items with name and price.
Provide Add to Cart button.
On click:
Store item details.
Open Cart Screen.

Screen 7: Cart Screen

Algorithm:
On screen initialize:
Fetch selected item using TinyDB or StartValue.
Display:
Item Name
Price
Show total amount.
Provide Checkout button.
On Checkout click:
Open Payment Screen with item details.

Screen 8: Payment Screen

Algorithm:
On initialize:
Display selected item and price.
Show payment option:
Cash on Delivery (COD)
When COD button clicked:
Show message "COD Selected".
On "Place Order" button click:
Open Success Screen.

Screen 9: Order Confirmation (Success Screen)

Algorithm:
Display message:
"Order Confirmed"
"Your order will arrive in 10 minutes 🚚"
Provide button:
Back to Home
On click:
Open Home Screen.

Screen 10: Navigation / Flow Control

Algorithm:
Maintain smooth navigation between all screens.
Use:
open another screen
open another screen with start value
Ensure data (item name & price) flows from:
Item Screen → Cart → Payment → Success.
